2 AN ACT
3 To enact Part V of Chapter 30 of Title 3 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950, to be
4 comprised of R.S. 3:4750.1 through 4750.5, relative to cell cultured food products;
5 to prohibit the sale of cell cultured food products for human consumption; to provide
6 for penalties; to provide for rules and regulations; to provide for certain exceptions;
7 to provide for effectiveness; and to provide for related matters.
8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. Part V of Chapter 30 of Title 3 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950,
10 comprised of R.S. 3:4750.1 through 4750.5, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 PART V. CELL CULTURED FOOD PRODUCTS
12 §4750.1. Short title
13 This Part shall be known and may be cited as the "Cell Cultured Food
14 Products Act".
15 §4750.2. Cell cultured food products; prohibition
16 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, no person
17 shall manufacture, distribute, sell, or offer for sale, any cell cultured food
18 product for human consumption in this state.
19 B. For purposes of this Part, "cell cultured food product" means any
20 cultured animal tissue produced from in vitro animal cell cultures outside of the
21 organism from which it is derived.
22 §4750.3. Violations; penalties
23 A. A violator of any provision of this Part or of any rule or regulation
24 adopted pursuant to the provisions of this Part shall be subject to a civil penalty
25 of not more than five hundred dollars for each violation. Each day on which a
26 violation occurs shall be a separate offense.
