1 B. Penalties may be assessed only by a ruling of the commissioner based
2 upon an adjudicatory hearing held in accordance with the provisions of the
3 Administrative Procedure Act.
4 C. In addition to civil penalties, the commissioner may assess the
5 proportionate costs of the adjudicatory hearing against the offender. The
6 commissioner shall determine the amount of costs to be assessed.
7 D. The commissioner may institute civil proceedings to enforce his
8 rulings in the district court for the parish in which the violation occurred.
9 E. The commissioner may institute civil proceedings seeking injunctive
10 relief to restrain and prevent the violation of the provisions of this Part, or of
11 the rules and regulations adopted pursuant to the provisions of this Part, in the
12 district court for the parish in which the violation occurred.
13 §4750.4. Rules and regulations
14 The commissioner may adopt rules and regulations necessary to
15 implement this Part. All rules and regulations shall be adopted in accordance
16 with the provisions of the Administrative Procedure Act.
17 §4750.5. Effectiveness
18 The provisions of this Part shall become effective only upon a final ruling
19 by the United States Supreme Court holding that prohibitions on cell cultured
20 food products do not violate the United States Constitution; however, nothing
21 in this Part shall prohibit accredited institutions of higher education in this state
22 from conducting research on cell cultured food products.
